<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_irux" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>irux</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>лицо</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>face</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>внимание</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>attention</q></cit></sense></sense><re xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><form type="lemma"><orth>irux æzdaxun</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>поворачиваться лицом к чему или кому-либо</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>to turn one's face towards someone or something</q></cit></sense><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_irux." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>е ’rux ku razdaxa æ xæʒarærdæmæ...</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>когда он повернет лицо к своему дому...</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>when he turned his face to his house ...</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 17</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>e ʼrux næ xatuj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>не обращает внимания</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>s/he does not pay attention</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 107</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>е ’rux ku razdaxa æ xæʒarærdæmæ...</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>когда он повернет лицо к своему дому...</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>when he turned his face to his house ...</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 17</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>e ʼrux næ xatuj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>не обращает внимания</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>s/he does not pay attention</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 107</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*ruka-, *rauka-</w><gloss><q>свет</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>светлый</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и пр.; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>roka-</w><gloss><q>свет</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>loka-</w><gloss><q>открытое пространство</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Семантика ‘лица’ ведет в этом случае к понятию ‘светлого’, ‘ясного’, ‘открытого’. Точно такое же развитие значения в %bавестийском%b: <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>čivra-</w><gloss><q>светлый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>ясный</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>čitra-</w><gloss><q>светлый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>сияющий</q></gloss></mentioned>, ) → ‘лицо’. Ср. также ос. <xr><ref target="#entry_ærgom"/></xr> ‘явный’ → ‘лицо’. Начальный %ii%i в %iirux%i представляет определенный артикль %ii%i, слившийся с именем *%irux%i. %bПерс.%b <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>rux</w><gloss><q>лицо</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>щека</q></gloss></mentioned>, , возможно, одного происхождения с ос. %iirux%i (см. <bibl><ref target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>136</biblScope></bibl>). См. <xr><ref target="#entry_rūs"/></xr> | %iros%i ‘щека’.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It probably traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*ruka-, *rauka-</w><gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>bright</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc.; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>roka-</w><gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>loka-</w><gloss><q>open space</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The semantics of ‘face’ leads in this case to the meaning ‘light’, ‘clear’, ‘open’. The same evolution of the meaning in %bAvestan%b: <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>čivra-</w><gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>bright</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>čitra-</w><gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>shining</q></gloss></mentioned>, ) → ‘face’. Cf. also Ossetic <xr><ref target="#entry_ærgom"/></xr> ‘evident’ → ‘face’. The initial %ii%i in %iirux%i is a definite article %ii%i, fused with the noun *%irux%i. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>rux</w><gloss><q>face</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>cheek</q></gloss></mentioned>, , is probably of one origin with Ossetic %iirux%i (see <bibl><ref target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>136</biblScope></bibl>). See <xr><ref target="#entry_rūs"/></xr> | %iros%i ‘cheek’.</etym></entry>